OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FThe haar descended over Edinburgh just
OL,7,Fas the Scottish Parliament was cooling
OL,8,Fdown for recess.
OL,10,FSweltering weather had done little to
OL,11,Fhelp the rising political temperature
OL,12,Finside Holyrood towards the end of
OL,13,Fterm.
OL,15,FMSPs are exhausted and it has been
OL,16,Fshowing.
OL,18,FTempers have been frayed. They need a
OL,19,Frest.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FTo be fair, they fought an election
OL,7,Fand then spent the next two months
OL,8,Ftrying to settle into their jobs ` in
OL,9,Fthe case of half of them learning to
OL,10,Fdo them from scratch as first-timers
OL,11,Fin the Scottish Parliament.
OL,13,FThis has led to a change of dynamics
OL,14,Fand it's not clear exactly how that
OL,15,Fwill manifest itself.
OL,17,FThe final first minister's questions
OL,18,Fof the term highlighted that with an
OL,19,Fapproach from Reform UK's Scotland
OL,20,Fleader Malcolm Offord that raised
OL,21,Feyebrows around the chamber.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FAt least he looked like he was having
OL,7,Ffun as he suggested items stolen by
OL,8,Fformer SNP chief executive Peter
OL,9,FMurrell in various museums.
OL,11,FNone of their opponents have alighted
OL,12,Fon a way to effectively deal with
OL,13,FReform at Holyrood.
OL,15,FOne left-leaning source messaged me on
OL,16,Fthe final day of term to say the
OL,17,Fapproach of "screaming at them,
OL,18,Fleaving Offord and co. to just calmly
OL,19,Frespond as if they are the normal
OL,20,Fones" was not working.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FYet it is not yet clear that Reform
OL,7,Fhas worked out how to maximise its
OL,8,Fimpact in Holyrood, either inside or
OL,9,Foutside the debating chamber.
OL,11,FThe biggest change, though, may be
OL,12,Finside the SNP group where an
OL,13,Finjection of new blood that includes
OL,14,Falmost a dozen ex-MPs has shifted the
OL,15,Fdynamic.
OL,17,FThose who used to ply their trade at
OL,18,FWestminster are used to more autonomy
OL,19,Fthan is generally the case at Holyrood
OL,20,Fand are already bristling against some
OL,21,Fof the party management in Edinburgh.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FLoyalty is also a little lower too.
OL,8,FThere is no imminent challenge ` nor
OL,9,Fis it being seriously talked about `
OL,10,Fto John Swinney but the ground beneath
OL,11,Fthe first minister's feet is a little
OL,12,Fless solid than would be expected
OL,13,Fgiven his election victory in May.
OL,15,FYou only need to look south to see how
OL,16,Fquickly things can change as the
OL,17,Frevolving door at Downing Street
OL,18,Fprepares to welcome its next prime
OL,19,Fminister.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FI spent most of last week in London
OL,7,Ftrying to work out what an Andy
OL,8,FBurnham premiership will look like
OL,9,Ffrom a Scottish perspective.
OL,11,FThe key takeaway is that, no matter
OL,12,Fhow many news articles try to tell you
OL,13,Fotherwise, no one is really sure.
OL,15,FWe did get some clues in his speech on
OL,16,FMonday where he talked about wanting
OL,17,Fto "extend devolution in Scotland,
OL,18,FWales, Northern Ireland".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FCrucially, that came with the caveat
OL,7,Fthat it would centre on pushing power
OL,8,Fout from Holyrood and into communities.
OL,10,FThe problem with that is he would
OL,11,Fstruggle to actually implement that
OL,12,Ffrom Westminster given the relevant
OL,13,Fpowers lie at Holyrood.
OL,15,FHowever, his talking up of powers for
OL,16,Frural economies to solve problems like
OL,17,Fpoor transport links will likely
OL,18,Fresonate with people in the south of
OL,19,FScotland.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FOne thing that did shine through when
OL,7,FI was speaking with people in London
OL,8,Fwas that everyone who has ever worked
OL,9,Fwith him really likes him.
OL,11,FAnd I mean, they *really* like him.
OL,13,FBaroness MacLeod of Camusdarach, who
OL,14,Fworked with him when she was a special
OL,15,Fadviser to former Chancellor Alister
OL,16,FDarling and Mr Burnham was Chief
OL,17,FSecretary to the Treasury, last week
OL,18,Ftold me he was "very approachable,
OL,19,Fgreat empathy, decent bloke".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FA separate usually reliably cynical
OL,7,Fsource said Mr Burnham might be the
OL,8,F"best boss" they had ever had.
OL,10,FAnother admiring former employee said
OL,11,Fhe was an "emotional sponge, he just
OL,12,Ftakes it in. It's what separates a
OL,13,Fgood policy or backroom specialist
OL,14,Ffrom a top notch politician."
OL,16,FA fourth person, who has worked on
OL,17,Fcampaigns with Mr Burnham, was more
OL,18,Fcautiously optimistic.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FThey said it was possible to "sit and
OL,7,Ftalk to him about normal stuff as well
OL,8,Fas work" and that the outgoing Greater
OL,9,FManchester Mayor is "generally
OL,10,Flikeable, which in politics these days
OL,11,Fis rare".
OL,13,FThey added: "He does seem to have a
OL,14,Fvision of what he thinks the country
OL,15,Fshould be like."
OL,17,FBut they did say Mr Burnham has
OL,18,Fpreviously suffered from "flip-
OL,19,Fflopping to try and please everyone".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G10/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FScottish MPs are broadly positive
OL,7,Fabout Mr Burnham, although some have
OL,8,Fconcerns about too much being made of
OL,9,Fhis mayoral record and say that the
OL,10,Fhead of a devolved administration can
OL,11,Fblame Westminster for things that go
OL,12,Fwrong while taking credit for things
OL,13,Fthat are going right.
OL,15,FFor obvious reasons, that doesn't work
OL,16,Fonce you're behind the door at No.10.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G11/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FBut overall, the reaction of this
OL,7,FLabour MP seemed to sum up the mood:
OL,8,F"It can only help us in Scotland.
OL,9,FStarmer was a massive drag on our
OL,10,Fsupport."
OL,12,FThe other question is who will be in
OL,13,FMr Burnham's top team?
OL,15,FMuch of the speculation has focused on
OL,16,Fwho the next Chancellor will be but
OL,17,Fother pitches are being made and some
OL,18,Fnakedly ambitious MPs have been
OL,19,Fannoying their colleagues.
OL,26,@pD@AOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G12/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FIt is widely assumed that Douglas
OL,7,FAlexander will vacate the Scotland
OL,8,FOffice with multiple MPs claiming he
OL,9,F"hates that job".
OL,11,FOne source said Mr Alexander is
OL,12,F"smarter than everyone around him"
OL,13,Fdespite the failure of Labour's
OL,14,FHolyrood election campaign, which he
OL,15,Fco-chaired, and will be in line for
OL,16,Fanother senior ministerial role.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G13/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FBlair McDougall, the business minister
OL,7,Fand former head of the Better Together
OL,8,Fcampaign against independence in 2014,
OL,9,Fwas previously a special adviser to Mr
OL,10,FBurnham's new chief of staff James
OL,11,FPurnell so is seen as a possibility
OL,12,Ffor higher office.
OL,14,FSo too is energy minister Michael
OL,15,FShanks, who is broadly seen as having
OL,16,Fdone a good job and has worked with Mr
OL,17,FBurnham on local energy policies in
OL,18,Frecent years.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G14/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,323,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F322A1782818297
OL,3,CMSPs need break to cool down as UK
OL,4,Cpolitical temperature spikes
OL,6,FCrucially, both of them have kept
OL,7,Ftheir heads down and avoided briefing
OL,8,Ftheir ambitions.
OL,10,FThat's something that will go down
OL,11,Fwell with Mr Burnham given his stated
OL,12,Fintention of changing the culture in
OL,13,FWhitehall.
OL,15,FBut the political weather in
OL,16,FWestminster is still sizzling and is
OL,17,Funlikely to cool even as we move
OL,18,Fbeyond the summer and into an Andy
OL,19,FBurnham government.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G15/15
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
